HEADWORD: Socratical
<hw>So*crat"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Socraticus</ets>, Gr.
<?/<?/<?/<?/.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Socrates, the Grecian sage
and teacher. (<sc>b. c.</sc> 469-399), or to his manner of teaching and
philosophizing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>Socratic</xex> method of reasoning and
instruction was by a series of questions leading the one to whom they
were addressed to perceive and admit what was true or false in doctrine,
or right or wrong in conduct.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Socratically</ent>⟦br⟧
